  "displayName": "Allen Helton",
  "headline": "",
  "summary": "I’m an Ecosystem Engineer at Momento with a background in building scalable, event-driven systems. These days, I spend a lot of time exploring how AI agents can actually work at enterprise scale. I focus on challenges like determinism, orchestration, and fault tolerance. I enjoy sharing what I learn. I write, livestream, and host podcasts to help developers understand complex systems in a way that feels approachable and practical. Community is at the core of everything I do. From the Believe in Serverless community to conference talks and one-on-one mentoring, I try to make space where people can learn and build together. I believe good humans build good technology, and I do my best to live that out in everything I do. Happy coding!",
